criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Patients with peripheral pulmonary lesions suspected to be cancer that need
             pathologically confirmed;

          2. Presence of bronchus leading to or adjacent to the lesion from CT scan.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Pure ground glass opacity (GGO) lesions;

          2. Refusal of participation;

          3. Severe cardiopulmonary dysfunction and other indications that can't receive
             bronchoscopy;

          4. Presence of concomitant endobronchial lesion during the brochoscopy procerdure.
